6 Contribute

<p>Contributing to theCrag is good for your <a href="/article/CragKarma">Karma</a>. The more quality content the site collects the better it gets.</p>

<p>If you have done a climb and the route description or any of the other data is missing then please consider adding it. Likewise if you see that a new route has not been entered yet, please help us fill in the gaps. We are especially interested in helping the dedicated climbers who put up new routes share the word.</p>

<p>It’s pretty easy to just update the index as you explore and browse. If you’re keen, read on for detailed information on how to contribute to the site:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/article/cragkarma">Crag Karma</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/indexpermissions">Index permissions</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/topotutorial">Making topos</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/topotips">Topo tips</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/updatingdescriptions">Writing descriptions</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/geolocation">Geolocating crags</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/editorstoolkit">Editors Toolkit</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/bulkedit">Bulk Edit</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/publisherparticipation">Publisher participation</a></li>
  <li><a href="/article/mixedcopyright">Mixed copyright</a></li>
</ul>

